<!--hand 01 top left Livingstone--><!--Stamp University College London, Galton Papers, 190-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>57 Sloane St</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">25<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> April</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1857</p>
<lb/><p rend="left">My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Galton</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I am sorry that 
<lb/>my engagments during 
<lb/>the whole of next 
<lb/>week will prevent 
<lb/>my having the pleasure 
<lb/>of accepting your 
<lb/>kind invitation to 
<lb/>dinner on thursday 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001007_0002"/><!--pb/@n='02'--> 
<lb/>I regret this as 
<lb/>it would give me 
<lb/>much pleasure 
<lb/>to have a little talk 
<lb/>with you </p>
<lb/><p>I am &amp; </p>
<lb/><p><persName>D. Livingstone</persName></p>
			
